headline: Differentiated earners set for more durable gains in US insurance
summary: Investing.com -- Insurance companies that delivered clearly differentiated results, like Equitable, MetLife, Voya, Lincoln, Arch, RenaissanceRe, Aon and Ryan Specialty, are best placed for more durable share-price performance into 2026. As cycle tailwinds fade and competition intensifies, investors are rewarding earnings quality over sheer beats, according to Morgan Stanley.
